# PrairieLog Vanilla Frontend Rule

This frontend must remain lightweight and framework-free.

Use:

* HTML
* CSS
* Vanilla JavaScript
* Fetch API
* Browser-native modules/patterns only if needed

Do not add:

* React
* Angular
* Vue
* npm dependencies
* bundlers
* TypeScript compilation
* frontend routing libraries
* state management libraries

## Script Loading

Use normal script tags.

Recommended order:

```html
<script src="js/config.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/state.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/rest-service.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/app.js" defer></script>
```

Page-specific scripts should load last.

For dashboard:

```html
<script src="js/dashboard.js" defer></script>
```

For docs:

```html
<script src="js/docs.js" defer></script>
```

For examples:

```html
<script src="js/examples.js" defer></script>
```

## Global Namespaces

Use a small number of explicit globals.

Allowed globals:

* `window.CONFIG`
* `window.PrairieLogState`
* `window.restService`
* `window.PrairieLogUI`

Avoid creating random global variables.

## REST Service Rules

`rest-service.js` should expose a class-based API client.

The default instance should be:

```js
window.restService = new RestService(window.CONFIG);
```

The REST service should include methods for:

* `createUser`
* `createApp`
* `getAppsByOwnerEmail`
* `getAppById`
* `createAppToken`
* `getAppTokens`
* `revokeAppToken`
* `createAlertDestination`
* `getAlertDestinations`
* `deleteAlertDestination`
* `testAlertDestination`
* `ingestLogEvent`
* `sendSampleErrorLog`
* `sendSampleInfoLog`
* `loadOpenApiContract`
* `getOpenApiEndpointSummary`

The REST service must not directly update HTML.

## DOM Rules

DOM queries and event listeners belong in page-specific files.

Examples:

* `dashboard.js` wires dashboard forms/buttons
* `docs.js` wires docs buttons
* `examples.js` wires copy-code buttons

Use clear IDs for interactive elements.

Example:

```html
<form id="create-user-form">
  <input id="user-email-input" />
  <input id="username-input" />
  <button type="submit">Create User</button>
</form>
```

Then:

```js
document
  .getElementById("create-user-form")
  .addEventListener("submit", handleCreateUser);
```

## Output Panels

Each interactive page should have an output/status panel.

Use output panels to show:

* success responses
* errors
* created IDs
* generated tokens
* test results

Never use `alert()` for normal app flow.

## Style Rules

Use one main stylesheet:

```text
frontend/css/styles.css
```

Keep styling simple:

* clean API/developer portal feel
* responsive layout
* readable code blocks
* clear form states
* clear success/error messages

Do not add CSS frameworks unless explicitly requested.
